Patch Set 4: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

(2 inline comments)

I don't know if it entirely makes sense to run these apis right next to each other without some namespacing. For example, running both means that you could do requests to both

  http://registry/images/
  http://registry/rpc/

It seems like it would be better if we could possibly put in a version identifier so that at least we could use

  http://registry/v2/rpc

Is that change possible, or will it break the rpc client?

Additional notes are inline.

Patch Set 4: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

(6 inline comments)

And do you think we need a test case for this function? IMO we'd better have one at least.

Patch Set 7:

Mark,

As it is now it looks like we would break bunch of tests and the client (checked within glance only) by moving the endpoint to /v2/rpc. Although there is not extremely many of those, so it would be doable with reasonable effort. 

My concern is that by doing that we might break existing implementations utilizing the v2 Reg API as this is how it has been initially implemented. I would not feel comfortable taking the risk to break user space.
